article.headline: UMBC 78, La Salle 67
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Brian Hodges scored 22 points and UMBC went on a 20-0 run midway through the second half in defeating La Salle 78-67 Thursday night. Jay Greene had 16 points and Thomas Young 13 for the Retrievers (4-5), coached by former La Salle assistant Randy Monroe. Darnell Harris and Sherman Diaz each had 13 points for the Explorers (4-2), who committed 22 turnovers. UMBC never trailed in the game, but led by only 42-37 with 13:50 left to play. The Retrievers then scored 20 unanswered points while holding La Salle scoreless for nine and a half minutes to lead 62-37. Only a late Explorer rally, led by Harris and Diaz, made the final score respectable.
